  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (7c6edeb 2023-03-17T01:23:48.291444506Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge bind\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThe rust output from `forge bind` is not formatted with `rustfmt`. I just set up a CI inspired by [foundry-rs/foundry-rust-template](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry-rust-template) but I can't satisfy both of them! If the output is rust-formatted, it fails the bind check, but if I pass the bind check, its not rust formatted.\r\n\r\nMy particular bind call looks like this:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nforge bind \\\r\n  --root ./contracts \\\r\n  --bindings-path ./crates/wallet/src/bindings \\\r\n  --module --single-file \\\r\n  --select \"^Spether$\"\r\n```",
